      • isSuccessful

        public boolean isSuccessful()
        True iff service responded with a return value, false if it threw an exception. In the former case property result is set to a valid value, otherwise proprety exception is set. There is NO distinction between business exception intentionally thrown by the service and some infrastructure exceptions caused by e.g. network timeouts.
        Returns:
        if the service responded with a proper return value.
